Install Terraform: 
Terraform is installed in the  local machine. downloaded Terraform from the official website
Install visual studio code from the official site
set the environment variables and create a working directory
configure the saml2aws configure command by running and sharing the secret key and access key of aws.
now addded the following script to run the main.tf file
post adding then terraform init , then terraform plan and terraform apply 
post applying the changes the script runs and creates the infrastructure in AWS under EKS
Verify the Cluster: Once the Terraform apply is complete, you can verify the cluster and deployed resources using the kubectl command-line tool.
Make sure the Kubernetes resources are created as expected
